A route's `serialize` should handle null contexts

In particular, when we are unrouting (in
anticipating of routing due to a URL change), the
default `unroute` implementation calls
`transitionTo` to transition to the parent, but
without a context. In these cases, if the parent
state has a context as part of its URL, it will
try to serialize this empty context, which causes
an error.

This na√Øve solution just serializes null contexts
to the empty string. Since we are unrouting and
the serialized value will never be used, this
resolves the problem. The long-term fix is to
have a smarter solution than just unrouting.
Update to latest github_api release

Injections can specify the order they are run.

Now, injections can register not just a function,
but also a name, and, optionally, the name of
the injection they should be run before.

This is useful in the case of, e.g., the data
store, which should create the instance of
DS.Store before the controllers are instantiated,
as they may have a dependency on the store at
initialization time.
Enumerate all properties per injection.

commits.message:
Guard against undefined mixins

This can easily happen with Ember.Object.extend(App.DoesNotExist, {...}).
Use Ember.assert instead of throw
Guard against implicit function application by Ember.assert

Guard mergeMixins parameters more generally

Previously we caught passing null or undefined into Object.create() or
.extend(). Now we also catch any other invalid types like strings,
numbers, or arrays.

We cannot use Ember.typeOf, since runtime depends on metal and we don't
want circular dependencies. For the weird array check, see
http://stackoverflow.com/a/1058753/525872

Split ArrayProxy into content and arrangedContent

This allows subclasses of ArrayProxy to modify
how the ArrayProxy presents itself without
changing the underlying array.
Crude sorting on ArrayController
Move sorting into separate mixin
Import tchak's sortable tests

Finish implementation of Sortable mixin

This borrows heavily from tchak's implementation
;)

Improve invalidation of view's controller prop

A view's controller is inherited from its parent
unless specifically overridden. This commit
improves the invalidation of the cached
computed property when:

a) the parent view changes, or
b) the controller of the parent changes.
